    "updated_at": "2013-10-01T04:39:38Z",
    "body": "I would think that the proper thing to do is for `rustpkg test [pkgname] [args ...]` to compile a test binary from the crate, then pass the `args` to the test binary like `rust test` does. That would allow you to pass arguments that only run certain tests or certain modules, pass `--bench` to only run benchmarks, pass `--ignored` to run ignored tests, or some combination thereof.\n",
